Sokoto State Governor Aminu Waziri Tambuwal has dissolved the state executive council with immediate effect, his Director- General on Media and Public Affairs, Mallam Abubakar Shekara said in a statement yesterday. He said the dissolution was aimed at restructuring and strategizing the cabinet for optimum efficiency and service delivery to the people of Sokoto State. Tambuwal thanked the members of the council for their dedication, sacrifice and loyalty to his administration. He also lauded the people of the state for cooperating with and supporting the outgoing members of the council towards achieving the successes recorded. The governor wished them success in their future endeavours. The statement said the commissioners would hand over the affairs of their respective ministries to the permanent secretaries.